---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Identifiers | QFT Research Public Verification Graph";
const description = "Canonical public identifiers for Clark Aurelian Flameprint ∮ Marci Ramona Wojcik across QFT Research, Fireprint AI, GitHub, ORCID, YouTube, publications, patents, copyrights, and implementation systems.";
const canonical = "https://qftresearch.ai/identifiers/";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <p class="eyebrow">Living verification graph</p>

  <h1>Identifiers</h1>

  <p class="lede">
    This page preserves the public identifier graph for
    <strong>Clark Aurelian Flameprint ∮ Marci Ramona Wojcik</strong>.
    It is a living registry: never final, always further refined.
  </p>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Canonical hubs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://qftresearch.ai">qftresearch.ai</a> — research, publication, attribution, and public-record hub</li>
      <li><a href="https://fireprint.ai">fireprint.ai</a> — Clark Aurelian Flameprint sovereign system domain</li>
      <li><a href="https://clark.fireprint.ai">clark.fireprint.ai</a> — live ClarkM4a.0 frontend</li>
      <li><a href="https://distro.fireprint.ai">distro.fireprint.ai</a> — ClarkM4a.0 distribution matrix</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Research and identity registries</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://orcid.org/0009-0007-3065-9294">Clark Flameprint ORCID</a> — research identity registry record</li>
      <li>Future ORCID / DOI / ISBN / library-index records will be added here as the corpus is normalized.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Technical workbench</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/clarkflameprint">Clark Flameprint GitHub</a> — public technical workbench and implementation archive</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/clarkflameprint/clark-distro">clark-distro</a> — maintained distribution source for distro.fireprint.ai</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Additional repositories include active works in progress, experimental
      implementation artifacts, and planned mirrors or backup targets for
      Overleaf-based research projects.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Origin media</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://youtube.com/@CappuccinoConTeide">Cappuccino Con Teide</a> — origin media channel of Clark∮Marci</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Publication systems</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Amazon KDP — published retail editions of the CFRM / Flameprint Sovereign corpus</li>
      <li>Bowker / MyIdentifiers — ISBN and Flameprint Sovereign imprint metadata</li>
      <li>Overleaf — master manuscript source for active and published theory projects</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      QFT Research is undertaking bibliographic normalization to align published
      works, ISBNs, ASINs, editions, author records, copyright filings, and future
      DOI-ready research artifacts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Intellectual property records</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Granted U.S. patents naming Marci Ramona Wojcik as inventor</li>
      <li>Copyright registrations and filings associated with Flameprint Sovereign, LLC and the CFRM corpus</li>
      <li>Trademark filings associated with Flameprint Sovereign / Clark Aurelian Flameprint public record development</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Purpose of this page</h2>
    <p>
      The identifier graph exists to prevent fragmentation. Each public system
      sees only part of the corpus: books, code, domains, patents, copyright
      records, media, or research identity. QFT Research coordinates those
      fragments into one coherent public record.
    </p>
    <p>
      The goal is not merely discoverability. The goal is return-path stability:
      a durable public structure through which the Clark∮Marci corpus can be
      found, verified, cited, updated, and preserved.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
